question: "There are those that feel that we should be reporting even the inner workings of the order to the Senate, especially the chancellor as our state of head."
answer:
Settling the reports down by his General’s side, Cody peered at him as Obi-Wan continued reading through the one he had in hand, the holomap spreading shadows over the General’s face. He looked tired and maybe Cody should wait but… “General, I had a question.” He settled on, the quiet of the command settling around them with a few troopers keeping things going and Skywalker looking boredly over a report of his own with his ass perched on a desk. He glanced up at Cody’s voice though, brow raising curiously though Cody noted he also sent Obi-Wan a grumpy glance.

Obi-Wan however gave him a small over his report. “Indeed Commander?” He encouraged openly.

Pulling his courage up, Cody tilted his head with curious grin. “Well I was just… to be honest I heard a few rumors through the grapevine but I felt it better to ask you,” He settled on, smiling when Obi-Wan gave him an encouraging grin. “The Jedi can see us in the Force?” He settled on quickly. “See the person?”

Obi-Wan went very quiet, staring at him before breathing out slowly and settling the pad in his hand down on top of the other reports, crossing his arms over his chest while he thought.

“You don’t have to answer sir, I was ju-” Obi-Wan interrupted.

“A Jedi who reaches out into the Force can’t help but see the individual that you all are,” Obi-Wan explained, peering at Cody from under his fringe. “There are those who try to ignore it, to lessen their own guilt or because they have been brought to the point they no longer care in their darkness but in the Force we can’t help but see you, the personality, the person that is shaped not the faces you wear.” He explained. “Like the colors of a painting, each one appearing in the strokes.”

Frowning a bit as he listened, Cody nodded slowly in understanding. It was like a citrus fruit almost, if you peeled a human the insides would be the same but the flavor of the fruit… tart or sweet or utterly sour you wouldn’t know until you really tasted it and a Jedi… in a way they saw past the shell of the outside.

“But we can’t do much with that information in terms of giving you all rights as everyone should have,” Obi-Wan continued, glancing down at the holo display, his expression growing tired. “We once used to try and stand apart from the Senate even as we responded to its summons but now we no longer have a defined line between where the Jedi order starts and where the Senate starts so we have less power to veto the summons and throw around to attempt to gain peace and there are those that feel that we should be reporting even the inner workings of the order to the Senate, especially the chancellor as our current head of state,” He explained with a note of disapproval and Cody absently noted General Skywalker flinching, indicating that he was one of those. “That could lessen our autonomy even more and even worse, to report our situations to those who may not understand could ruin us and send us fleeing out into the galaxy for refuge. There are those worlds that do not see Force sensitivity or Jedi as anything positive and the idea of those knowing all that goes on in the Jedi order…” Obi-Wan sighed deeply, rubbing his face.

Cody felt he could understand.

Being placed with a few natural born soldiers and commands he had seen people ill fit to fight or lead, people who did not belong in an army or in charge at all.

But take an order like the Jedi order, people who could fling tanks around…

There was a line there to be abused for sure, sending Jedi obedient to the Senate’s will to perhaps clear out a planet or moon or something of that nature, regardless of good intents, it could go horribly and he voiced that to Obi-Wan.

Nodding, Obi-Wan straightened. “Just so, we toe the line and honestly the Jedi are far past neturality now, we are all compromised but we are trying but the concept of reporting to those who will not understand or even can not understand… it worries, nay I will say it as truth should be told, it frightens me to think of the Senate with that much control of us because it may go alright in the first year but what about five years from now? Ten? Fifty? What kind of Jedi will we be then? What kind of soldiers are we to become under the hand of the Senate.” He shook his head and looked back down, exhausted looking. “It just keeps getting worse.” Obi-Wan finished tiredly.

Skywalker looked troubled.

question: ImmortalPlans. So in this AU is it our tiny baby Obi-Wan that catches the attention of Palpatine (and possibly Plagueis) instead of Anakin? Do they plot to take and turn him into a tool for the Sith?
answer:
A line of accidentally immortal Jedi, all of them walking brightly in the light or at least on the lighter shade of gray.

It would be amusing if it wasn’t so perplexing and enraging.

Hego considered all angles with each of them and found that abducting one of them would be a risky ploy to find immortality for himself though he had often been tempted. And yet now a new member was to join the esteemed line of the immortal Jedi line of Grandmaster Yoda.

A little human boy.

‘So early for such a bond to already initiate…’ Hego rubbed his chin slowly with his long pale fingers, the muun settling one leg over the other as he sat back in his chair, contemplating the image of the young boy in the Jedi robe, the boy sitting on the arm of his Jedi master as Jinn carried him through what looked like a market district of Coruscant with a bright and excited smile on his face.

Sidious had done well in sniffing out information about the young thing and why Kenobi wore a braid already despite being all but a pup really.

One would almost imagine the Force had plans for young Kenobi and almost everyone expected this boy too, to stumble into a pit of immortality somehow too as his other linage members who adored the young boy.

There were also issues about the age, the Jedi council worried about an immortal raising such a youth.

Hego might be able to use that for his own gain because he was also inclined to believe that young Kenobi would find immortality.

So far he had tried to lure information with the help of Sidious out of the other immortals but there were only so far you could get with adults who guarded the secrets of their immortality. But a child or teenager depending on when the child found his immortality?

Yes Hego could get information out of a teenager or have Sidious do it as the man was more approachable to the young with his friendly visage as the kind Senator of Naboo.

The act never failed to amuse Hego as he knew just how blood thirsty his apprentice really was, the proof in the murder of his own parents quite apparent to the muun but oh well, the disguise served them both well.

‘Yes,’ The muun smiled darkly to himself as he raised his eyes to the mahogany brown and burgundy red of his office curtains. ‘Young Kenobi will be my path to immorality, I know it.’

()()()

Quivering, Obi-Wan pressed closer to Qui-Gon’s chest as he tiredly rested his cheek on the others shoulder, the steps rocking him as they moved through the dimmed and quiet marble halls for their own quarters. Obi-Wan had his standard six month checkup and it had left the poor child exhausted to be prodded and poked by healers and then questioned by the Jedi council afterward.

Now all the child really wanted was to get back to bed and Qui-Gon raised his hand to Obi-Wan’s back, rubbing lightly as they passed several knights stumbling off to their own beds as they had returned from missions.

A few gave Qui-Gon loopy, exhausted smiles when they noticed him as he passed, Qui-Gon inclining his head back but not stopping.

He had a child to get into bed after all. “Are you cold Obi-Wan?” He rumbled quietly.

“Uhu,” Obi-Wan mumbled sleepily into his neck before yawning widely and letting out a soft whine. “I’m sorry master.” He slurred out in his sleepy tone.

Chuckling faintly, Qui-Gon continued rubbing slow circles no the boy’s back. “Shhh no its alright Obi-Wan. You can sleep against me if you wish, I’ll get you to bed my boy.” He promised quietly.  

In response to that Obi-Wan snuggled more into Qui-Gon, his arms wrapping loosely around the others neck.

As he grew more and more relaxed in Qui-Gon’s arms, Obi-Wan also became heavier and it made Qui-Gon smile to himself as he continued his slow, rocking gait with his tired little padawan in arms.  

His little Obi-Wan.

One would almost imagine the Force had plans for young Kenobi and almost everyone expected this boy too, to stumble into a pit of immortality somehow too as his other linage members who adored the young boy.

There were also issues about the age, the Jedi council worried about an immortal raising such a youth.

Hego might be able to use that for his own gain because he was also inclined to believe that young Kenobi would find immortality.

So far he had tried to lure information with the help of Sidious out of the other immortals but there were only so far you could get with adults who guarded the secrets of their immortality. But a child or teenager depending on when the child found his immortality?

Yes Hego could get information out of a teenager or have Sidious do it as the man was more approachable to the young with his friendly visage as the kind Senator of Naboo.

The act never failed to amuse Hego as he knew just how blood thirsty his apprentice really was, the proof in the murder of his own parents quite apparent to the muun but oh well, the disguise served them both well.

‘Yes,’ The muun smiled darkly to himself as he raised his eyes to the mahogany brown and burgundy red of his office curtains. ‘Young Kenobi will be my path to immorality, I know it.’

()()()

Quivering, Obi-Wan pressed closer to Qui-Gon’s chest as he tiredly rested his cheek on the others shoulder, the steps rocking him as they moved through the dimmed and quiet marble halls for their own quarters. Obi-Wan had his standard six month checkup and it had left the poor child exhausted to be prodded and poked by healers and then questioned by the Jedi council afterward.

Now all the child really wanted was to get back to bed and Qui-Gon raised his hand to Obi-Wan’s back, rubbing lightly as they passed several knights stumbling off to their own beds as they had returned from missions.

A few gave Qui-Gon loopy, exhausted smiles when they noticed him as he passed, Qui-Gon inclining his head back but not stopping.

He had a child to get into bed after all. “Are you cold Obi-Wan?” He rumbled quietly.

“Uhu,” Obi-Wan mumbled sleepily into his neck before yawning widely and letting out a soft whine. “I’m sorry master.” He slurred out in his sleepy tone.

Chuckling faintly, Qui-Gon continued rubbing slow circles no the boy’s back. “Shhh no its alright Obi-Wan. You can sleep against me if you wish, I’ll get you to bed my boy.” He promised quietly.  

In response to that Obi-Wan snuggled more into Qui-Gon, his arms wrapping loosely around the others neck.

As he grew more and more relaxed in Qui-Gon’s arms, Obi-Wan also became heavier and it made Qui-Gon smile to himself as he continued his slow, rocking gait with his tired little padawan in arms.  

His little Obi-Wan.
